The paper presents parallel algorithms for constructing wavelet trees and rank select structures, which are data structures commonly used in data compression and information retrieval. This falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and parallel computing (cs.PF, cs.Distributed, cs.Parallel). The algorithms also involve integer sorting, which is a common topic in divide and conquer algorithms (cs.DC).
